text: Chloe Fraser (born 20 September 1993) is a British professional racing cyclist from Scotland, who currently rides for British amateur team The Racing Chance Foundation. From Dingwall, Fraser was the winner of the road race, at the 2015 Scottish Road Championships. Fraser will return to the professional peloton in 2021, with the team. ==See also== * List of 2015 UCI Women's Teams and riders ==References== ==External links== * * Category:1993 births Category:Living people Category:Scottish female cyclists Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
